    "Id": "vehiclechassisdef_STRIKER_3053",
    "Name": "Striker (3053)",
    "Details": "<b>Name: <color=#85DBF6>Striker Light Tank (3053 Upgrade)</color>\nArmor: <color=#85DBF6>Ferro-Fibrous</color>\tTechnology: <color=#85DBF6>Inner Sphere</color>\nMovement: <color=#85DBF6>5/8 (Wheeled)</color>\tEngine: <color=#85DBF6>155 Fusion</color></b>\n\nThe Striker Light Tank, a joint venture between Valiant Systems and Wunderland Enterprises, was introduced in the early 31st century as a low-cost light fire support tank. It quickly became a mainstay in the AFFS, outstripping production capacity.\n\nThis major refit of the Striker replaces the ICE with a fusion engine. The original's standard armor is also replaced by ferro-fibrous armor. These upgrades free up enough space for the LRM launcher to be upgraded to an LRM-15 and further enhanced with an Artemis IV fire control system. Lastly, the SRM launcher is exchanged for a pair of Streak SRM-2 launchers.",
